<dl id="n53123o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53123o">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53123o"> 123(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> threw his hair to heaven <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53123o"><li>FW 26.08 </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n53123o">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n53123o">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53123o">MS BL 47476a-149</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:321 <a name="ad7" href="../../FF/fdra/ada.htm#ad7">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad7.htm#n53123o">Draft: I.1&sect;1.7</a>/2.7</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Ensuite, il prit des mains de Chandaka une &eacute;p&eacute;e &agrave; la poign&eacute;e d&apos;or et de pierreries; la lame &eacute;tait bien affil&eacute;e; d&apos;un seul coup, <mark>il trancha sa chevelure. Il la lan&ccedil;a dans l&apos;air</mark>, et elle rayonna comme un astre nouveau. Les Dieux la recueillirent, et ils la v&eacute;n&eacute;r&egrave;rent pieusement. <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 62f</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Siddharta took the squire&apos;s sword and cut off his own hair and threw it skyward to heaven, where it shone like a new star. </mm> </dd></dl>
